  "text": "Employees are actively engaged with data in ways that go beyond a mere 'data fetishism' emphasizing objectivity and truth; they also quantify themselves as a form of mindfulness, resistance against norms and in narrative communication with others [CITATION_1] . In short, employees are 'quantifiers' and 'quantifying', not just 'quantified' [CITATION_2] .",
